  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="9">World Scientific</subfield>
    <subfield code="a">We explore the landscape of technical naturalness for nonrelativistic systems, finding surprises which challenge and enrich our relativistic intuition already in the simplest case of a single scalar field. While the immediate applications are expected in condensed matter and perhaps in cosmology, the study is motivated by the leading puzzles of fundamental physics involving gravity: the cosmological constant problem and the Higgs mass hierarchy problem.</subfield>
